                            <comment id="17188474" author="paulk" created="Tue, 1 Sep 2020 13:53:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Strange, the following two lines print different results:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
println unsortedList[0] &amp;lt;=&amp;gt; unsortedList[1]         &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// =&amp;gt; -1
&lt;/span&gt;println unsortedList[0].compareTo(unsortedList[1])    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// =&amp;gt; 1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Method resolution is picking the &lt;tt&gt;compareTo&lt;/tt&gt; method from the parent when calling &lt;tt&gt;comparable.compareTo(right)&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;DefaultTypeTransformation#compareToWithEqualityCheck&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17191030" author="paulk" created="Sat, 5 Sep 2020 10:08:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed PR merged. Thanks for raising the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
